			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Initially, I misread your formula to say 3x(level)+5.
<br />

<br />
3x(level+5) does not seem right.  Meleers don't even start out with defense caps that high.  Theirs is 5x(level) + 5, which is only a cap of 10 at level 1, whereas with your formula, INT caster would have a defense cap of 18 at level 1.  Traditionally, the +5 on the end is not +5 to level, but +5 to Defense... Puttling +5 in parenthesis with the level means you are adding 5 levels before doing the multiplication.  That could be right, but it doesn't seem right.
<br />

<br />
Xeth</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
