			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I've tested it with lower-level characters and higher-level: it's possible there's a cap below level 10, but certainly my Chanter's Defence followed the formula from 10 to 12 after I went out of my way to ensure I maxed it.
<br />

<br />
Sure, there might be a theoretical advantage to INT casters at level 1, but it's almost impossible for any character to max out Defence at level 1... you just can't kill enough mobs without levelling up, unless you stand there taking the hits until you die. I guess it would be interesting to get a Temp on a level 1 INT caster and see what they do max out at by standing there being hit.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
